{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CfvkxunN8dwVBkgTqCVyZN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 123 test files, 3410 tests pass. Coverage at 96.94%, all files above 80%.\n\n---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 11-1 Unified SprintState Schema with Versioning\n**Outcome:** All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story status updated to `verifying`.\n\n### Fixes Applied\n\n1. **MEDIUM (fixed): `parseStoryRetriesRecord` accepted negative counts** -- Added `count >= 0` guard in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:72`\n\n2. **MEDIUM (fixed): `parseFlaggedStoriesList` did not deduplicate** -- Rewrote to use Set-based dedup in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:81-91`\n\n3. **HIGH (fixed): `retriesPath()` and `flaggedPath()` are dead code misleading consumers** -- Added `@deprecated` JSDoc annotations in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/retry-state.ts`\n\n4. **MEDIUM (fixed): `writeRetries`/`writeFlaggedStories` duplicated read-modify-write pattern** -- Extracted `mutateState()` helper in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/retry-state.ts` to centralize the pattern\n\n5. **Tests added**: 2 new tests in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts` covering negative count rejection and flagged story deduplication\n\n### Verification\n\n- TypeScript: no new type errors in story files\n- Tests: 3410 passed (123 test files), 0 failures\n- Coverage: 96.94% overall (target: 90%), all 129 files above 80% per-file floor\n- BATS integration: 307 passed\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: `parseStoryRetriesRecord` accepted negative retry counts (fixed)\n- MEDIUM: `parseFlaggedStoriesList` allowed duplicate entries (fixed)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `retriesPath()` and `flaggedPath()` are exported dead code -- marked deprecated but not removed (deferred to story 11-3 per deliberate non-goals)\n- `RETRIES_FILE` and `FLAGGED_FILE` constants in retry-state.ts are only used by deprecated path helpers -- also deferred to 11-3\n- `writeRetries`/`writeFlaggedStories` return void and silently swallow write failures -- changing the API signature to return `Result<void>` would be a breaking change, deferred to a future story\n- Several `as unknown as SprintState` casts in `getSprintState()` v2 branch (state.ts:123) bypass type safety at runtime -- could be replaced with a proper validation/parse function\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No tests for concurrent read-modify-write scenarios in retry-state.ts (would require integration-level testing)\n- No test for `getSprintState()` when JSON has unexpected field types in nested objects (the `as unknown as` casts mask this)\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- Read-modify-write race condition in all retry-state.ts functions (and in state.ts `updateStoryStatus`, `updateRunProgress`, `clearRunProgress`). Two concurrent callers can lose writes. This is an inherent limitation of the file-based state approach and would require file locking or a different storage backend to fix properly.\n- `retry-state.ts` still accepts a `dir` parameter that is completely unused (vestigial). This is documented in the story technical notes as intentional for backward compatibility.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab623fea926e92d2a (use SendMessage with to: 'ab623fea926e92d2a' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 122852\ntool_uses: 48\nduration_ms: 490803</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e449f80-823c-4489-a784-b43b6c7039d6","uuid":"3adb2d63-cb04-4885-b75e-2ef8b30456cd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:47:24.783Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HI