(line 205).","+```output","+31:    version: 2,","+91:    writeFileSync(tmp, data, 'utf-8');","+92:    renameSync(tmp, final);","+```"," ","+**Verdict:** PASS — writeStateAtomic writes to tmp then renames. migrateV1ToV2 sets version:2 (migration.ts:205).","+"," ## AC 11: v2 state not re-migrated"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+sed -n '116,145p' src/modules/sprint/state.ts | head -5","+```","+```output","+      if (version === 2) {","+        const defaults = defaultState();","+        const run = parsed.run as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;","+        const sprint = parsed.sprint as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;","+        const session = parsed.session as Record<string, unknown> | undefined;","+```"," ","-Evidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:116`: `if (version === 2)` returns state as-is without calling `migrateV1ToV2`.","+**Verdict:** PASS — version===2 returns state immediately without calling migrateV1ToV2."," ","-Test evidence: `migration.test.ts` has no re-migration. `state.test.ts` tests confirm v2 round-trips.","-"," ## AC 12: migrateV1ToV2() reads external files"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -n 'readIfExists' src/modules/sprint/migration.ts | grep -v 'function readIfExists'","+```","+```output","+191:  const retriesContent = readIfExists(OLD_FILES.storyRetries);","+195:  const flaggedContent = readIfExists(OLD_FILES.flaggedStories);","+199:  const statusContent = readIfExists(OLD_FILES.ralphStatus);","+```"," ","-Evidence from `src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:187-219`:","-- Line 191: reads `.story_retries` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.storyRetries)`","-- Line 195: reads `.flagged_stories` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.flaggedStories)`","-- Line 199: reads `ralph/status.json` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.ralphStatus)`","-- Merges each into appropriate v2 field","+**Verdict:** PASS — Reads .story_retries (space-separated), .flagged_stories (one per line), ralph/status.json."," "," ## AC 13: Source files NOT deleted after migration"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -n 'unlinkSync\\|rmSync\\|unlink\\b' src/modules/sprint/migration.ts; echo \"EXIT:$?\"","+```","+```output","+EXIT:1","+```"," ","-Evidence: `migrateV1ToV2()` (lines 187-219) has no `unlinkSync` or `rmSync` calls. Test: \"does NOT delete source files after migration\" confirms both files still exist after migration.","+**Verdict:** PASS — No file deletion calls in migration.ts. Exit code 1 confirms grep found no matches."," "," ## AC 14: retry-state.ts reads from sprint-state.json"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -n 'getSprintState\\|writeStateAtomic\\|\\.story_retries\\|\\.flagged_stories' src/lib/retry-state.ts","+```","+```output","+2:import { getSprintState, writeStateAtomic } from '../modules/sprint/state.js';","+5:const RETRIES_FILE = '.story_retries';","+6:const FLAGGED_FILE = '.flagged_stories';","+13:  const result = getSprintState();","+15:  writeStateAtomic(mutator(result.data));","+39:  const result = getSprintState();","+95:  const result = getSprintState();","+```"," ","-Evidence from `src/lib/retry-state.ts`:","-- Line 2: `import { getSprintState, writeStateAtomic } from '../modules/sprint/state.js';`","-- `readRetries` (line 38-44): calls `getSprintState()`, returns `new Map(Object.entries(result.data.retries))`","-- `setRetryCount` (line 68-72): calls `readRetries`, sets value, calls `writeRetries`","-- `getRetryCount` (line 60-63): calls `readRetries`, returns value","+**Verdict:** PASS — All read functions call getSprintState(). RETRIES_FILE/FLAGGED_FILE constants are only used in deprecated path helpers, not in data operations."," ","-No file reads of `.story_retries` anywhere in the function bodies.","-"," ## AC 15: Flagged functions read from sprint-state.json"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -n 'readFlaggedStories\\|writeFlaggedStories\\|removeFlaggedStory' src/lib/retry-state.ts","+```","+```output","+94:export function readFlaggedStories(_dir: string): string[] {","+106:export function writeFlaggedStories(_dir: string, stories: string[]): void {","+116:export function removeFlaggedStory(dir: string, key: string): void {","+117:  const stories = readFlaggedStories(dir);","+119:  writeFlaggedStories(dir, filtered);","+```"," ","-Evidence from `src/lib/retry-state.ts`:","-- `readFlaggedStories` (line 94-100): calls `getSprintState()`, returns `[...result.data.flagged]`","-- `writeFlaggedStories` (line 106-111): uses `mutateState` which calls `getSprintState()` and `writeStateAtomic()`","-- `removeFlaggedStory` (line 116-120): calls `readFlaggedStories` and `writeFlaggedStories`","+**Verdict:** PASS — readFlaggedStories calls getSprintState() (line 95), writeFlaggedStories uses mutateState (line 107-110) which calls getSprintState+writeStateAtomic."," ","-No file reads of `.flagged_stories` anywhere.","-"," ## AC 16: Consumers compile and pass tests"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -rn 'readRetries\\|setRetryCount\\|getRetryCount\\|readFlaggedStories\\|writeFlaggedStories\\|removeFlaggedStory\\|resetRetry' src/ --include='*.ts' | grep -v '__tests__' | grep -v 'retry-state.ts'","+```","+```output","+src//commands/retry.ts:5:  readRetries,","+src//commands/retry.ts:6:  readFlaggedStories,","+src//commands/retry.ts:7:  resetRetry,","+src//commands/retry.ts:67:    resetRetry(dir, storyKey);","+src//commands/retry.ts:74:    resetRetry(dir);","+src//commands/retry.ts:84:  const retries = readRetries(dir);","+src//commands/retry.ts:85:  const flagged = new Set(readFlaggedStories(dir));","+```"," ","-Evidence:","-- All 3410 tests pass (0 failures)","-- `npx tsc --noEmit` shows 0 errors in `types/state.ts`, `sprint/state.ts`, `sprint/migration.ts`, `lib/retry-state.ts`","-- 87 pre-existing errors are all in unrelated files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, teardown.test.ts, deps.test.ts, lib/state.ts)","+**Verdict:** PASS — Only consumer is retry.ts command, which uses same API signatures. All 3410 tests pass."," "," ## AC 17: All tests pass with 0 regressions"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+npx vitest run --reporter=verbose 2>&1 | grep -E '(Test Files|Tests.*passed)'","+```","+```output","+ Test Files  123 passed (123)","+      Tests  3410 passed (3410)","+```"," ","-Evidence: `npx vitest run` → 123 test files, 3410 tests passed, 0 failed. BATS: 307 passed.","+**Verdict:** PASS — 123 test files, 3410 tests, 0 failures."," "," ## AC 18: Zero new type errors"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | grep \"error TS\" | grep -E '(types/state\\.ts|sprint/state\\.ts|sprint/migration\\.ts|lib/retry-state\\.ts)'; echo \"MATCHES:$?\"","+```","+```output","+MATCHES:1","+```"," ","-Evidence: `npx tsc --noEmit` shows 87 errors total, all pre-existing. Zero errors in story-changed files (confirmed by filtering output for `types/state.ts`, `sprint/state.ts`, `sprint/migration.ts`, `lib/retry-state.ts` — no matches).","+**Verdict:** PASS — Zero type errors in story-changed files. 87 pre-existing errors all in unrelated files."," "," ## AC 19: Migration test cases present"," ","-**Verdict:** PASS","+```shell","+grep -c 'it(' src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts","+```","+```output","+25","+```"," ","-Evidence from `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts`:","-- (a) \"converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2\" — line 356","-- (b) \"converts v1 state without retries/flagged files to v2 with empty defaults\" — line 380","-- (c) v2 not re-migrated: covered by `getSprintState` v2 path in state.test.ts","-- (d) \"handles missing version field (treated as v1)\" — line 424","-- (e) \"handles retries file with malformed lines gracefully\" — line 439","+```shell","+grep \"it('\" src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts | head -25","+```","+```output","+  it('returns fail when no old files exist', () => {","+  it('migrates story retries into attempts', () => {","+  it('migrates sprint-status.yaml into story statuses', () => {","+  it('migrates ralph/status.json into run section', () => {","+  it('migrates flagged stories as blocked', () => {","+  it('migrates session issues into action items', () => {","+  it('handles missing old files gracefully (partial migration)', () => {","+  it('writes sprint-state.json after migration', () => {","+  it('handles invalid JSON in ralph/status.json gracefully', () => {","+  it('handles retries file with malformed lines', () => {","+  it('computes sprint counts correctly', () => {","+  it('outputs version 2 from migrateFromOldFormat', () => {","+  it('populates v2 retries field from .story_retries', () => {","+  it('populates v2 flagged field from .flagged_stories', () => {","+  it('populates v2 session from ralph/status.json', () => {","+  it('initializes v2 epics as empty and observability as null', () => {","+  it('does NOT delete .story_retries or .flagged_stories after migration', () => {","+  it('converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2', () => {","+  it('converts v1 state without retries/flagged files to v2 with empty defaults', () => {","+  it('reads session data from ralph/status.json during migration', () => {","+  it('handles missing version field (treated as v1)', () => {","+  it('handles retries file with malformed lines gracefully', () => {","+  it('does NOT delete source files after migration', () => {","+  it('rejects negative retry counts', () => {","+  it('deduplicates flagged stories', () => {","+```"," ","-Additional tests: \"rejects negative retry counts\" (line 474), \"deduplicates flagged stories\" (line 491), \"does NOT delete source files\" (line 457).","+**Verdict:** PASS — 25 migration tests covering: (a) v1 with retries/flagged→v2, (b) v1 without files→v2 empty defaults, (c) v2 not re-migrated (via getSprintState v2 path), (d) missing version→v1, (e) malformed retries lines handled."]}],"originalFile":"# Verification Proof: 11-1 Unified SprintState Schema with Versioning\n\n**Story:** 11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning\n**Verified:** 2026-03-24\n**Method:** Unit-testable (tagged `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->`)\n\n## Summary\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| ACs Total | 19 |\n| ACs Passed | 19 |\n| ACs Failed | 0 |\n| ACs Escalated | 0 |\n| Test Files | 123 passed |\n| Tests | 3410 passed |\n| Coverage | 96.94% (target: 90%) |\n| Per-file floor | All 129 files above 80% |\n\n## AC 1: SprintStateV2 has version: 2 and required top-level fields\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/types/state.ts:97-125`:\n```typescript\nexport interface SprintStateV2 {\n  readonly version: 2;\n  readonly sprint: { ... };\n  readonly stories: Record<string, StoryState>;\n  readonly retries: Record<string, number>;\n  readonly flagged: string[];\n  readonly epics: Record<string, EpicState>;\n  readonly session: SessionState;\n  readonly observability: ObservabilityState;\n  readonly run: { ... };\n  readonly actionItems: ActionItem[];\n}\n```\n\nAll required fields present: `version: 2`, `sprint`, `stories`, `retries`, `flagged`, `epics`, `session`, `observability`, `run`, `actionItems`.\n\n## AC 2: EpicState, SessionState, ObservabilityState interfaces\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/types/state.ts:48-68`:\n- `EpicState` has `status: string`, `storiesTotal: number`, `storiesDone: number`\n- `SessionState` has `active: boolean`, `startedAt: string | null`, `iteration: number`, `elapsedSeconds: number`\n- `ObservabilityState` has `statementCoverage: number | null`, `branchCoverage: number | null`, `functionCoverage: number | null`, `lineCoverage: number | null`\n\n## AC 3: SprintStateAny union type\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/types/state.ts:128-131`:\n```typescript\nexport type SprintStateAny = SprintStateV1 | SprintStateV2;\nexport type SprintState = SprintStateV2;\n```\n`SprintStateV1` preserves v1 schema with `version: 1` (lines 71-94). `SprintStateV2` has `version: 2`.\n\n## AC 4: defaultState() returns SprintStateV2 with version: 2\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:29-69`:\n```typescript\nexport function defaultState(): SprintState {\n  return {\n    version: 2,\n    sprint: { total: 0, done: 0, failed: 0, blocked: 0, inProgress: null },\n    stories: {},\n    retries: {},\n    flagged: [],\n    epics: {},\n    session: { active: false, startedAt: null, iteration: 0, elapsedSeconds: 0 },\n    observability: { statementCoverage: null, branchCoverage: null, functionCoverage: null, lineCoverage: null },\n    run: { active: false, startedAt: null, iteration: 0, cost: 0, completed: [], failed: [], currentStory: null, currentPhase: null, lastAction: null, acProgress: null },\n    actionItems: [],\n  };\n}\n```\n\n## AC 5: v1 state auto-migrates to v2\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:147-154`:\n```typescript\n// v1 or missing version — migrate to v2\nconst v1State = parsed as unknown as import('../../types/state.js').SprintStateV1;\nconst migrated = migrateV1ToV2(v1State);\nconst writeResult = writeStateAtomic(migrated);\n```\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` — \"converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2\" passes.\n\n## AC 6: Missing version field treated as v1\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:113-116`: Only `version === 2` returns early. Any other value (including undefined) falls through to v1 migration.\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` — \"handles missing version field (treated as v1)\" passes.\n\n## AC 7: .story_retries parsed into retries Record\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:64-75` (`parseStoryRetriesRecord`):\n- Parses space-separated `key count` per line\n- Test: \"10-3-python-provider 2\\n10-5-migrate-consumers 1\" → `{ \"10-3-python-provider\": 2, \"10-5-migrate-consumers\": 1 }`\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` — \"converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2\" verifies exact Record output.\n\n## AC 8: .flagged_stories parsed into flagged array\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:81-92` (`parseFlaggedStoriesList`):\n- Parses one key per line, deduplicates with Set\n- Test: \"9-5-multi-stack\\n10-3-python-provider\" → `[\"9-5-multi-stack\", \"10-3-python-provider\"]`\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` — \"converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2\" verifies exact array output.\n\n## AC 9: ralph/status.json parsed into session\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:151-161` (`parseRalphStatusToSession`):\n- Maps `status: \"running\"` → `active: true`, `loop_count: 3` → `iteration: 3`, `elapsed_seconds: 3698` → `elapsedSeconds: 3698`\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` — \"reads session data from ralph/status.json during migration\" verifies exact values.\n\n## AC 10: Migrated state written atomically with version: 2\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:86-98` (`writeStateAtomic`):\n```typescript\nwriteFileSync(tmp, data, 'utf-8');\nrenameSync(tmp, final);\n```\nWrites to tmp file then renames. `migrateV1ToV2` returns `version: 2` (line 205).\n\n## AC 11: v2 state not re-migrated\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:116`: `if (version === 2)` returns state as-is without calling `migrateV1ToV2`.\n\nTest evidence: `migration.test.ts` has no re-migration. `state.test.ts` tests confirm v2 round-trips.\n\n## AC 12: migrateV1ToV2() reads external files\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/migration.ts:187-219`:\n- Line 191: reads `.story_retries` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.storyRetries)`\n- Line 195: reads `.flagged_stories` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.flaggedStories)`\n- Line 199: reads `ralph/status.json` via `readIfExists(OLD_FILES.ralphStatus)`\n- Merges each into appropriate v2 field\n\n## AC 13: Source files NOT deleted after migration\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence: `migrateV1ToV2()` (lines 187-219) has no `unlinkSync` or `rmSync` calls. Test: \"does NOT delete source files after migration\" confirms both files still exist after migration.\n\n## AC 14: retry-state.ts reads from sprint-state.json\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/lib/retry-state.ts`:\n- Line 2: `import { getSprintState, writeStateAtomic } from '../modules/sprint/state.js';`\n- `readRetries` (line 38-44): calls `getSprintState()`, returns `new Map(Object.entries(result.data.retries))`\n- `setRetryCount` (line 68-72): calls `readRetries`, sets value, calls `writeRetries`\n- `getRetryCount` (line 60-63): calls `readRetries`, returns value\n\nNo file reads of `.story_retries` anywhere in the function bodies.\n\n## AC 15: Flagged functions read from sprint-state.json\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/lib/retry-state.ts`:\n- `readFlaggedStories` (line 94-100): calls `getSprintState()`, returns `[...result.data.flagged]`\n- `writeFlaggedStories` (line 106-111): uses `mutateState` which calls `getSprintState()` and `writeStateAtomic()`\n- `removeFlaggedStory` (line 116-120): calls `readFlaggedStories` and `writeFlaggedStories`\n\nNo file reads of `.flagged_stories` anywhere.\n\n## AC 16: Consumers compile and pass tests\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence:\n- All 3410 tests pass (0 failures)\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` shows 0 errors in `types/state.ts`, `sprint/state.ts`, `sprint/migration.ts`, `lib/retry-state.ts`\n- 87 pre-existing errors are all in unrelated files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, teardown.test.ts, deps.test.ts, lib/state.ts)\n\n## AC 17: All tests pass with 0 regressions\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence: `npx vitest run` → 123 test files, 3410 tests passed, 0 failed. BATS: 307 passed.\n\n## AC 18: Zero new type errors\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence: `npx tsc --noEmit` shows 87 errors total, all pre-existing. Zero errors in story-changed files (confirmed by filtering output for `types/state.ts`, `sprint/state.ts`, `sprint/migration.ts`, `lib/retry-state.ts` — no matches).\n\n## AC 19: Migration test cases present\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/migration.test.ts`:\n- (a) \"converts v1 state with retries/flagged files to v2\" — line 356\n- (b) \"converts v1 state without retries/flagged files to v2 with empty defaults\" — line 380\n- (c) v2 not re-migrated: covered by `getSprintState` v2 path in state.test.ts\n- (d) \"handles missing version field (treated as v1)\" — line 424\n- (e) \"handles retries file with malformed lines gracefully\" — line 439\n\nAdditional tests: \"rejects negative retry counts\" (line 474), \"deduplicates flagged stories\" (line 491), \"does NOT delete source files\" (line 457).\n"}}
