{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RARiwtxcd4nKFYNU4ooxpi","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→\n    51→### Verification Gaps\n    52→\n    53→- **`recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path for `stacks` field** not directly unit-tested — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir (9-2).\n    54→- **`init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field** after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks (9-2).\n    55→- Both stories currently in `verifying` status — final verification pass not yet completed.\n    56→\n    57→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n    58→\n    59→- No sandbox, permission, or CLI issues reported this session.\n    60→- Pre-existing TS compilation errors (~10 test files) continue to be noise but do not block execution.\n    61→\n    62→---\n    63→\n    64→## 3. What Went Well\n    65→\n    66→- **Code review pipeline is catching real bugs.** 7 HIGH/MEDIUM issues found and fixed before merge. The `init-project.ts` persistence bug would have been a production defect.\n    67→- **Epic 9 fully completed.** All 5 multi-stack stories done across sessions 6-8. Multi-stack detection, state migration, init orchestration, Dockerfile generation, and consumer migration all landed.\n    68→- **Story 10-1 clean execution.** StackProvider interface + registry created with 30 new tests, 97.06% coverage, backward compatibility confirmed (79 existing stack-detect tests still pass).\n    69→- **Backward compatibility maintained.** `stack-detect.ts` re-exports from new `stacks/types.ts` — existing imports unbroken.\n    70→- **Test suite healthy.** 3098+ tests passing, 0 failures, all 127 files above 80% coverage floor.\n    71→\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→## 4. What Went Wrong\n    75→\n    76→- **Two LOW-severity issues intentionally not fixed in 9-2.** The `migrateState()` unchecked cast and double-detection in recovery are accepted tech debt. Neither is likely to cause production issues but both reduce code quality.\n    77→- **Coverage gaps in init-project tests for stacks field.** Code review flagged this but it was not addressed — the `stacks` field integration in init is tested implicitly but not explicitly.\n    78→- **Pre-existing TS errors are accumulating.** ~10 test files have unrelated compilation issues. These create noise in every dev session and risk masking new errors. Story 15-4 exists for this but remains in backlog.\n    79→- **Only 1 new story completed this session.** Session 7 carryover (9-2 review) consumed time. Throughput was effectively 1 story in session 8.\n    80→\n    81→---\n    82→\n    83→## 5. Lessons Learned\n    84→\n    85→### Repeat\n    86→- **Code review as a mandatory pipeline stage.** It caught the `init-project.ts` persistence bug and the `isValidState()` type-checking gap — both would have been shipped otherwise.\n    87→- **Stub-first provider pattern.** Creating NodejsProvider as a stub in 10-1 (with `throw 'not yet implemented'`) keeps the story focused and the next stories (10-2 through 10-4) well-scoped.\n    88→- **Backward compatibility through re-exports.** The `stack-detect.ts` re-export pattern avoids a big-bang migration.\n    89→\n    90→### Avoid\n    91→- **Leaving coverage gaps flagged by review unfixed.** The init-project stacks assertion gap was called out but not addressed. Future sessions should fix all review findings or explicitly defer with a tracked issue.\n    92→- **Allowing test-only utilities in public exports.** `_resetRegistry` should never have been in the barrel file. Establish a convention (separate `testing.ts` export or conditional export).\n    93→\n    94→---\n    95→\n    96→## 6. Action Items\n    97→\n    98→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n    99→- None critical. Both stories are functionally complete with all HIGH/MEDIUM issues resolved.\n   100→\n   101→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint / Next Session)\n   102→1. **Complete stories 10-2, 10-3, 10-4** — Full NodejsProvider, PythonProvider, RustProvider implementations. These are the immediate next work items.\n   103→2. **Add explicit `stacks` field assertions to `init-project.test.ts`** — Coverage gap flagged in 9-2 review.\n   104→3. **Move `_resetRegistry` out of public barrel export** — Either `stacks/testing.ts` or conditional export.\n   105→4. **Validate stack names in `migrateState()`** — Check `raw.stack` against known `StackName` values before casting.\n   106→\n   107→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n   108→1. **Story 15-4: Fix pre-existing TS compilation errors** — 10 test files with unrelated errors. Growing noise.\n   109→2. **Story 15-2/15-5: Lint rules for bare catch and exception swallowing** — The `catch {}` in registry.ts was caught manually; a lint rule would catch these automatically.\n   110→3. **Deduplicate `StackDetection` type** — Blocked until story 10-5 migrates all consumers to the new registry.\n   111→4. **Eliminate double detection in `recoverCorruptedState()`** — Call `detectStacks()` once and derive `detectStack()` from it.\n   112→5. **Add `recoverCorruptedState()` integration test with planted `package.json`** — Currently no direct test for stacks field recovery.\n   113→\n   114→---\n   115→\n   116→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Session 9)\n   117→\n   118→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n   119→**Session:** 9 (autonomous ralph run, continuation from session 8)\n   120→**Session start:** ~07:54 UTC\n   121→**Appended:** 2026-03-24\n   122→\n   123→---\n   124→\n   125→## 1. Session Summary\n   126→\n   127→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages |\n   128→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|\n   129→| 10-2-nodejs-provider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed |\n   130→\n   131→Story 10-2 was the sole story attempted this session. Ralph picked it as the next Tier D backlog item after 10-1 completed in session 8. The story went through all three pipeline stages: story creation (rewrote the minimal 3-AC spec into a detailed 18-AC version), development (full NodejsProvider implementation), and code review (4 issues found, all HIGH/MEDIUM fixed). Status is `verifying` — awaiting final verification pass.\n   132→\n   133→**Net progress:** Epic 10 now has 2 of 5 stories done (10-1, 10-2). Stories 10-3 (Python), 10-4 (Rust), and 10-5 (consumer migration) remain in backlog.\n   134→\n   135→---\n   136→\n   137→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   138→\n   139→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n   140→\n   141→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   142→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   143→| HIGH | 10-2 | `parseTestOutput()` vitest regex didn't capture skipped count — total calculation was wrong | Yes |\n   144→| HIGH | 10-2 | `parseTestOutput()` jest regex failed when `skipped` appeared between `passed` and `total` — rewrote to extract fields independently | Yes |\n   145→| MEDIUM | 10-2 | `utils.ts` at 70.58% coverage (below 80% floor) — `readTextSafe()` had no tests. Added `utils.test.ts` with 9 tests | Yes |\n   146→| MEDIUM | 10-2 | `nodejs.ts` catch branch in `patchStartScript` for malformed JSON was untested. Added test | Yes |\n   147→\n   148→Code review caught 4 issues (2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM). All fixed in-session. The `parseTestOutput()` bugs were real correctness issues — test result parsing would have reported wrong totals for vitest projects and certain jest output formats.\n   149→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01U3WVphM6eq7EFgxeuPxV2v","session_id":"0e449f80-823c-4489-a784-b43b6c7039d6","uuid":"bcb54a60-bc24-4659-bfee-da409cc0310e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:57:15.010Z"}
