{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E8AiZfmdhPMDV1Z3KCYSKm","type":"tool_result","content":"   448→\n   449→### Cumulative stats\n   450→- Tests: 3098 -> 3329 (+231 new tests)\n   451→- Bugs caught by code review: 15 (7 in session 8, 4 in session 9, 4 in session 10) -- all fixed\n   452→- Bugs shipped: 0\n   453→- Stories blocked: 0 (10-3 blocker resolved)\n   454→- Tech debt items deferred: 8 (type mismatches x2, regex fragility x2, comment matching, task markers, consumer branches, AGENTS.md staleness)\n   455→\n   456→### Sprint velocity\n   457→- Epic 10 progress: 0/5 -> 3/5 in one day\n   458→- Pipeline throughput: ~1 story per ralph session (consistent across all 4 sessions)\n   459→- Estimated sessions remaining for Epic 10: 2 (10-4 + 10-5, assuming 10-5 is not split)\n   460→\n   461→---\n   462→\n   463→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Sessions 12-13)\n   464→\n   465→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n   466→**Sessions:** 12 (10-4 full pipeline) and 13 (10-5 story creation + 10-4 verification)\n   467→**Session start:** ~09:14 UTC\n   468→**Appended:** 2026-03-24T13:11Z\n   469→\n   470→---\n   471→\n   472→## 1. Session Summary\n   473→\n   474→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages Completed |\n   475→|-------|------|---------|---------------------------|\n   476→| 10-4-rust-provider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification (implicit via commit) |\n   477→| 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | ready-for-dev | create-story only |\n   478→\n   479→**Session 12 (~09:14-09:34Z):** Story 10-4 went through the full pipeline -- create-story, dev-story (55 new tests, 3397 total, 0 regressions), and code-review (2 MEDIUM fixed, 2 LOW deferred). Committed as `fa47c33`.\n   480→\n   481→**Session 13 (~09:43Z):** Story 10-5 had its create-story stage completed. The story creation agent expanded the backlog item into a detailed 17-AC spec covering consumer migration for all files that contain stack string comparisons. Story status moved from `backlog` to `ready-for-dev`.\n   482→\n   483→**Net progress:** Epic 10 now has 4 of 5 stories done (10-1, 10-2, 10-3, 10-4). Only 10-5 (consumer migration) remains, at `ready-for-dev`.\n   484→\n   485→---\n   486→\n   487→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   488→\n   489→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n   490→\n   491→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   492→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   493→| MEDIUM | 10-4 | Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` -- example was backwards | Yes |\n   494→| MEDIUM | 10-4 | Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching -- 2 tests added | Yes |\n   495→\n   496→Code review caught 2 MEDIUM issues, both fixed in-session. No HIGH-severity bugs this time -- the Rust provider had a cleaner implementation compared to Node.js and Python providers.\n   497→\n   498→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   499→\n   500→1. **`hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies.** Pre-existing behavior inherited from the pattern used in `stack-detect.ts` and other providers. LOW severity, consistent with the same issue in Python and Node.js providers.\n   501→2. **`getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format.** TOML allows `[dependencies.foo]` as an alternative to inline table syntax. The current regex only handles the `[dependencies]` section block. Pre-existing limitation, not introduced by this story.\n   502→3. **Bevy system libs detection deferred.** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in `dockerfile-template.ts`. Correctly deferred to avoid scope creep.\n   503→\n   504→### Code Quality Concerns\n   505→\n   506→1. **Coverage gap: no integration test for `installOtlp` success path.** Requires `cargo` binary. Same pattern as Python provider's `pip`/`pipx` gap. Consistent limitation across all providers.\n   507→2. **`AppType` union lacks `'library'` variant.** Epic definition mentioned it for Rust, but actual code only has `'generic'`. Story creation agent correctly followed the code, not the aspirational epic text.\n   508→\n   509→### Verification Gaps\n   510→\n   511→- **10-4 verification was implicit.** The story was committed with all tests passing (55 new, 3397 total, 0 regressions). Sprint-status shows `done`. However, the session issues log does not record a formal verification stage for 10-4 -- the review stage at 09:34Z was the last recorded pipeline step.\n   512→- **10-5 create-story flagged 3 risks** that the dev agent should watch for:\n   513→  - AC17 (`verify-prompt.ts`) compares `AppType` not `StackName` -- could cause false positives in boundary tests\n   514→  - AC16 (`teardown.ts`) accesses state field not local variable -- migration needs state shape understanding\n   515→  - `detectAppType()` export chain may break if `stack-detect.ts` deleted before re-export verified\n   516→\n   517→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n   518→\n   519→- No sandbox, permission, or CLI issues reported in these sessions.\n   520→- Docker Desktop status remains unknown (not tested in 10-4 since all 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`).\n   521→\n   522→---\n   523→\n   524→## 3. What Went Well\n   525→\n   526→- **10-4 completed cleanly.** 55 new tests, zero regressions, 2 review issues (both MEDIUM, both fixed). The cleanest provider implementation across all four (10-1 through 10-4).\n   527→- **All 27 ACs verified as `cli-verifiable`.** No Docker dependency needed. The verification-tier pattern from session 11 is now standard.\n   528→- **Story creation agent handled ambiguity well.** Three points of ambiguity in the epic definition (library AppType, Bevy detection, workspace ordering) were all resolved correctly by following the actual codebase rather than aspirational epic text.\n   529→- **Epic 10 at 80% completion.** Four of five stories done in sessions 8-13. The StackProvider pattern (interface + registry + Node.js + Python + Rust) is fully implemented.\n   530→- **Test suite continues to grow.** 3098 -> 3397 (+299 new tests across sessions 8-13). Zero regressions throughout.\n   531→- **10-5 story spec is thorough.** 17 ACs covering every consumer file, with boundary tests (AC12-13) to enforce zero stack string comparisons outside `src/lib/stacks/`. This gives the dev agent strong guidance for the final migration.\n   532→\n   533→---\n   534→\n   535→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   536→\n   537→- **10-4 lacks a formal verification record.** The session issues log shows dev-story at 09:24Z with no issues and code-review at 09:34Z, but no explicit verification stage. Sprint-status shows `done`, so verification must have happened, but there is no proof document or verification log entry. This is a process gap.\n   538→- **Comment-matching in dependency detection is now tech debt across all three providers.** `hasCargoDep`, `hasPythonDep`, and the Node.js equivalent all match package names inside comments. This was flagged as LOW in each review and deferred each time. It is now a systematic issue, not an isolated one.\n   539→- **Story 10-5 is accumulating scope from all prior sessions.** It now owns: consumer migration for 8+ files, type reconciliation (CoverageToolInfo, OtlpResult), stack-detect.ts deletion, import migration for 7+ test files, boundary test creation, and the `StackDetection` type deduplication. This is the largest story in Epic 10 by far.\n   540→- **`installOtlp` success path is untested in all three providers.** This is a systematic gap -- no provider has integration tests for actual package installation. The gap will persist until a CI/Docker environment is available for integration testing.\n   541→\n   542→---\n   543→\n   544→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   545→\n   546→### Repeat\n   547→- **Following actual code over aspirational epic text.** The story creation agent's decision to use `'generic'` instead of `'library'` for Rust and to defer Bevy detection prevented scope creep and kept the story focused."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01U3WVphM6eq7EFgxeuPxV2v","session_id":"0e449f80-823c-4489-a784-b43b6c7039d6","uuid":"d69c33b8-5c80-4e5c-8585-66312255606b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:57:27.185Z"}
