{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K2MxDoPWtg9QyDfQoV5pbM","type":"tool_result","content":"   547→- **Following actual code over aspirational epic text.** The story creation agent's decision to use `'generic'` instead of `'library'` for Rust and to defer Bevy detection prevented scope creep and kept the story focused.\n   548→- **Consistent provider implementation pattern.** The Rust provider followed the same structure as Node.js and Python, making it the fastest and cleanest implementation. The pattern is proven.\n   549→- **Expanding minimal story specs before development.** The 10-5 create-story stage produced a 17-AC spec from a backlog item with no detail. This is now standard practice across sessions 8-13.\n   550→\n   551→### Avoid\n   552→- **Systematic deferral of the same issue across stories.** Comment-matching in dependency detection was flagged LOW and deferred in 10-2, 10-3, and 10-4. Three deferrals of the same issue should trigger a tracked fix, not another deferral.\n   553→- **Skipping formal verification for stories that \"obviously pass.\"** Even when all tests pass and code review is clean, the verification stage should produce a record. Story 10-4 has no verification artifact.\n   554→\n   555→---\n   556→\n   557→## 6. Action Items\n   558→\n   559→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   560→1. **Verify that 10-4 proof/verification artifact exists.** If not, document the gap. Do not retroactively create a fake proof.\n   561→\n   562→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint / Next Session)\n   563→1. **Complete story 10-5 (consumer migration).** This is the final story in Epic 10. It is large -- consider whether it can be completed in a single session or needs splitting.\n   564→2. **Evaluate splitting 10-5.** Carried forward from sessions 9-11. The story now has at least 5 distinct concerns: (a) consumer file migration, (b) test file import migration, (c) stack-detect.ts deletion, (d) type reconciliation (CoverageToolInfo, OtlpResult), (e) boundary test creation. Consider splitting into 2-3 sub-stories if the dev agent struggles.\n   565→3. **Address the 10-5 risks flagged by create-story.** The `verify-prompt.ts` AppType vs StackName distinction, `teardown.ts` state field access, and `detectAppType()` export chain all need careful handling during implementation.\n   566→4. **Fix comment-matching in dependency detection.** This is now a systematic issue across all providers. Create a single fix that adds comment-awareness to `hasCargoDep`, `hasPythonDep`, and the Node.js equivalent. Track as a backlog item at minimum.\n   567→\n   568→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n   569→1. **`installOtlp` integration tests for all providers.** Requires Docker/CI. Systematic gap across Node.js, Python, Rust.\n   570→2. **`getCargoDepsSection` `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format.** TOML edge case, low real-world impact.\n   571→3. **Add `'library'` to `AppType` union.** If Rust library projects need distinct treatment in the future.\n   572→4. **Story 15-4: Fix pre-existing TS compilation errors.** Still at ~50 errors. Noise is chronic.\n   573→5. All items from sessions 8-11 backlog remain open (15-2/15-5, StackDetection dedup, double detection, recoverCorruptedState test, `_resetRegistry` export cleanup, readTextSafe catch branch, registry.ts 94.73%, hasPythonDep normalization, TOML regex replacement, proof parser docs).\n   574→\n   575→---\n   576→\n   577→## Cross-Session Summary (Sessions 8-13, 2026-03-24)\n   578→\n   579→### Stories completed today: 4\n   580→- **10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry** -- done (session 8)\n   581→- **10-2-nodejs-provider** -- done (session 9)\n   582→- **10-3-python-provider** -- done (sessions 10-11)\n   583→- **10-4-rust-provider** -- done (sessions 12-13)\n   584→\n   585→### Stories started: 1\n   586→- **10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider** -- ready-for-dev (story created in session 13)\n   587→\n   588→### Cumulative stats\n   589→- Tests: 3098 -> 3397 (+299 new tests)\n   590→- Bugs caught by code review: 17 (7 in session 8, 4 in session 9, 4 in session 10, 2 in sessions 12-13) -- all fixed\n   591→- Bugs shipped: 0\n   592→- Stories blocked: 0\n   593→- Tech debt items deferred: 11 (type mismatches x2, regex fragility x3, comment matching x3, task markers, consumer branches, AGENTS.md staleness)\n   594→\n   595→### Sprint velocity\n   596→- Epic 10 progress: 0/5 -> 4/5 in one day (6 sessions)\n   597→- Pipeline throughput: ~1 story per ralph session (consistent across all 6 sessions)\n   598→- Estimated sessions remaining for Epic 10: 1 (10-5 only, but it is the largest story)\n   599→\n   600→---\n   601→\n   602→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Sessions 14-15)\n   603→\n   604→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n   605→**Sessions:** 14 (Epic 10 completion + 10-5 dev) and 15 (11-1 create-story + dev-story)\n   606→**Session start:** ~10:12 UTC\n   607→**Session budget:** 30 minutes\n   608→**Appended:** 2026-03-24T14:12Z\n   609→\n   610→---\n   611→\n   612→## 1. Session Summary\n   613→\n   614→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages Completed |\n   615→|-------|------|---------|---------------------------|\n   616→| 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done | dev-story, code-review, verification (completed earlier sessions for create-story) |\n   617→| Epic 10 retrospective | Epic 10 | done | retrospective run, epic marked done |\n   618→| 11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning | Epic 11 (Unified State) | review | create-story, dev-story completed |\n   619→\n   620→**Key events:**\n   621→- Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) was fully completed -- all 5 stories done, retrospective run, epic marked done. Committed as `2974467` (10-5) and `97c24f5` (epic close).\n   622→- Story 11-1 progressed from backlog to review status. Both create-story (expanded to 19 ACs, 7 tasks) and dev-story stages completed. Still needs code review and verification.\n   623→- Sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md were **overwritten by test data mid-session** and had to be restored from git. This caused disruption and data loss risk.\n   624→- No stories were fully completed to done status during this session's 30-minute window due to time constraints on 11-1.\n   625→\n   626→**Net progress:** Epic 10 closed (5/5 done). Epic 11 started -- 1 of 3 stories in review, 2 in backlog.\n   627→\n   628→---\n   629→\n   630→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   631→\n   632→### Category: Type System / Architecture\n   633→\n   634→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   635→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   636→| MEDIUM | epic-10 retro | CoverageToolName type fragmentation -- provider values don't match HarnessState strings | Tracked for Epic 14 |\n   637→| MEDIUM | 11-1 create-story | Circular dependency risk: retry-state.ts -> getSprintState() -> migrateFromOldFormat() potential cycle | Flagged, needs monitoring in dev |\n   638→\n   639→### Category: Story Scope / Planning\n   640→\n   641→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   642→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   643→| MEDIUM | epic-10 retro | Story 10-5 had 17 ACs and 8 consumer files -- heaviest story in the epic | Completed despite density |\n   644→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Epic number reuse confusion -- previous sprint had a different Epic 11 (Retrospective Integration) | Documented, no action needed |\n   645→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Stub overwrite -- existing 3-AC story file replaced with 19-AC, 7-task spec | Intentional improvement |\n   646→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Deferred deletion of `.story_retries`/`.flagged_stories` to 11-3 to avoid data loss risk | Correct decision |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01U3WVphM6eq7EFgxeuPxV2v","session_id":"0e449f80-823c-4489-a784-b43b6c7039d6","uuid":"baaafa2f-f1aa-4341-a538-561f1b06e51e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:57:31.037Z"}
